##########
question: Hi there, here is my website 17 and if you select “projects” you see that the images are formatted beautifully. However, when you click on the individual project page 2 you see the pictures are oversized. Is there a way to correct this? Thank you.

reponse: From a quick inspection, it’s due to the following css:
.article-banner { width: 100%; height: auto; }

whereas in your home page you have:
.col-lg-6 { width: 50%; }

restricting the dimensions.

###########












.article-container {
  max-width: 60%;
}



.container {
    max-width: auto;
  }



.article-container {
    max-width: 50%;
  }
  
.universal-wrapper {
    width: 70%;
  max-width: 70%;
  }
  








  .ml11 {
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 3.5em;
  }
  
  .ml11 .text-wrapper {
    position: relative;
    display: inline-block;
    padding-top: 0.1em;
    padding-right: 0.05em;
    padding-bottom: 0.15em;
  }
  
  .ml11 .line {
    opacity: 0;
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    height: 100%;
    width: 3px;
    background-color: #fff;
    transform-origin: 0 50%;
  }
  
  .ml11 .line1 { 
    top: 0; 
    left: 0;
  }
  
  .ml11 .letter {
    display: inline-block;
    line-height: 1em;
  }

  

